cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for classification and segmentation of Whole-slide images of Hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC). This falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the determination of tile size for CNN applications, which is a common problem in Deep Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). The use of Attention CNN for voting the most contributing tile size also involves Information Retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL, and cs.IR.
